android.net.uri
URI, uniform resource identifier to handle image paths, website url and resume doc file path which has to be uploaded by the user.

import okhttp3.MultipartBody
okhttp to make network request calls.
MultipartBody = help to exchange used when need to send different types of files over the internet, text + image + docs

import java.io.InputStream
used to read/process resume uploaded, image uploaded. if not used, image would appear as broken.

import java.io.FileOutputStream


import java.io.File
used to work with files and folders directly in device. can be used to delete resume to be uploaded later.

private var selectedEducationImageUri: Uri? = null
name of teh storage box, Uri? means path can be null. =null means start with a null.
we can remove =null and declare as lateinit.

companion object {
        private const val REQUEST_EDUCATION_IMAGE = 100
        private const val REQUEST_RESUME_IMAGE = 101
        private const val REQUEST_RESUME_DOCUMENT = 102
    }

Your app says: "System, please let user pick an education image" → sends ticket #100
User picks a file → system returns with result and says "this is for ticket #100"
Your app knows: "Ah, this is the education image result!"


val educationTextBody = education.toRequestBody("text/plain".toMediaType())
toRequestBody converts all teh data into HTTP format to send over internet to backend.
Without it: Server wouldn't understand how to handle mixed file types

With it: Each piece gets proper MIME type labeling
Server knows "this is text", "this is PDF", "this is image"


